HYDERABAD: An innocuous reply from Cyberabad police Twitter handle to a question on security arrangements ma-de for American software companies based in Hyderabad in the backdrop of heightened tensions between Iran and America drew sharp reactions from netizens, including Hyderabad MP Asaduddin Owaisi , on Wednesday.It was on Tuesday a Twitter user, who is affiliated with a political party, tweeted, “Many wannabe Jihadis work for American Software companies in Hyderabad? After #Iran threatened to hit US assets, has @hydcitypolice @cyberabadpolice @RachakondaCop done background check/risk assessment of these Peacefuls? Or cops are clueless? @KTRTRS @TelanganaDGP @USCGHyderabad (sic)’’.Cyberabad police, in reply to his tweet, said: “Yes sir... We have specialised wings for collection of advance intel and our teams are on the job 24X7. Thanks for alerting us. Please keep us updated if you find anything suspicious (sic).”This reply evoked sharp criticism from Twitter users, including Owaisi, who said, “@cpcybd sir you say ‘yes sir’ please enlighten how many such ‘jihadi’ are working in software companies kindly give a number if not please clarify what you exactly meant Will you reply to an MP or only to a Bhakt? (sic)’’This was followed by another tweet by Owaisi, “@cpcybd sir whatever you do but no killings in name of ‘encounter’ at 05am please, if possible arrest & as accepted 3rd degree will be given but pls no cartoos in stomach CP saheb Terrorism has no religion, (remember NGodse),’’ indirectly taking a reference to Cyberabad commissioner VC Sajjanar.Sajjanar was in news following the early morning encounter of four accused on December 6 last year in connection with the vet rape case.In a damage-control exercise, Cyberabad police said, “Our tweet was misconstrued. The intent is only to suggest that we are always alert and well equipped to ensure security and it does not mean to agree with the suggestion. We reiterate that we are committed to maintaining peace and order in the society without prejudice towards any person or community.”
